PrPSc seems to be the main, if not the unique, component of the infectious agent of TSEs, the prion (3). TSEs, such as bovine spongiform encephalopathy (BSE) in cattle, CreutzfeldtJakob disease, Gerstmann-Straussler-Scheinker syndrome, and fatal familial insomnia in humans, are fatal, progressive, and neurodegenerative disorders
